      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "fefc90a0ba56b8d1665cea192a6316b2bd51fb8b",
            "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: implement Peer Discovery"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Olaf Weber",
          "email": "olaf@sgi.com",
          "date": "2017-01-27 15:36:47.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Amir Shehata",
          "email": "amir.shehata@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-03 15:44:17.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-9119 lnet: add \"lnetctl peer list\"",
        "message": "LU-9119 lnet: add \"lnetctl peer list\"\n\nAdd IOC_LIBCFS_GET_PEER_LIST to obtain a list of the primary\nNIDs of all peers known to the system. The list is written\ninto a userspace buffer by the kernel. The typical usage is\nto make a first call to determine the required buffer size,\nthen a second call to obtain the list.\n\nExtend the \"lnetctl peer\" set of commands with a \"list\"\nsubcommand that uses this interface.\n\nModify the IOC_LIBCFS_GET_PEER_NI ioctl (which is new in the\nMulti-Rail code) to use a NID to indicate the peer to look\nup, and then pass out the data for all NIDs of that peer.\n\nRe-implement \"lnetctl peer show\" to obtain the list of NIDs\nusing IOC_LIBCFS_GET_PEER_LIST followed by one or more\nIOC_LIBCFS_GET_PEER_NI calls to get information for each\npeer.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: I76c6cf8d8f18abbbbf97684c4501f80935d22aa2\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
}